                type="document" xml:id="d236">
                <head>236. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On December 7, 1961, the Department of State, reacting to the Japanese
                    Government’s protest of the President’s November 21 request for a Tariff
                    Commission investigation on the establishment of an equalization fee on cotton
                    textiles from Japan, sent telegram 1465 to the Embassy in Tokyo. This telegram,
                    serving as guidance, outlined several points with which to respond to the
                    protest, and is scheduled for publication in <ref target="frus1961-63v22">volume
                        XXII</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
